WEBVTT

00:08.500 --> 00:10.800
My name is 
Melinda Gordon.

00:10.900 --> 00:12.100
I'm married,

00:12.200 --> 00:14.300
I live in a small town,

00:14.400 --> 00:16.200
and I own an antique shop.

00:16.300 --> 00:18.400
I might be just like you.

00:18.500 --> 00:20.200
Except that from the time
I was a little girl,

00:20.300 --> 00:22.500
I knew that I could talk to the dead.

00:22.600 --> 00:23.900
It's all right, honey.

00:24.000 --> 00:27.200
Earthbound spirits,
my grandmother called them.

00:27.306 --> 00:29.700
They're stuck here because they have
unfinished business with the living

00:29.804 --> 00:33.500
and they come to me for help.

00:35.004 --> 00:40.407
In order to tell you my story,
I have to tell you theirs.

00:44.107 --> 00:47.406
Ok, this is ridiculous.
Tim stiffed you again?

00:47.509 --> 00:51.101
Yeah. And it had to be the night
I find a possible homicide.

00:51.206 --> 00:55.200
And guess who gets to drive
all the way down to central?

00:55.308 --> 00:59.602
Oh, that really is a long drive.
Listen, don't try to be a hero, ok?

00:59.708 --> 01:02.303
Get yourself a bed down there.
Bet you're sleepy.

01:02.407 --> 01:07.703
Well, why don't you give me a little
something to stay up for? Like...

01:07.806 --> 01:11.103
what are you wearing?

01:11.306 --> 01:12.402
Nothing.

01:12.505 --> 01:16.403
No! No, no, no. Tonight it's
pink flannel pyjama, isn't it?

01:16.508 --> 01:17.703
Ok, yes, it is.

01:17.808 --> 01:20.102
But you know what? You either get
sexy wife or sensible wife,

01:20.205 --> 01:22.502
and you're not home, so it's sensible.

01:22.606 --> 01:24.503
Fair enough.

01:24.607 --> 01:26.601
Climb into bed.
I'll be home soon.

01:26.708 --> 01:28.300
Ok. Love you.

01:28.405 --> 01:31.201
Love you, too.

01:35.205 --> 01:36.600
Evening, sir.

01:36.708 --> 01:40.001
Clancy. Long time no see.

01:40.108 --> 01:42.603
- What's happening, Harold?
- The usual party.

01:42.708 --> 01:45.700
Just don't ask what we use for piÃ‘atas.

01:45.806 --> 01:50.400
- Need a hand?
- Yeah, if you wouldn't mind.

01:51.906 --> 01:55.403
All right, on 3.
And... 3.

01:59.506 --> 02:01.603
You couldn't take time
to aspirate the guy for me?

02:01.708 --> 02:03.302
Sorry. I'm flying solo.

02:03.407 --> 02:06.601
Flaherty was supposed to come with
but he bagged out on me.

02:06.708 --> 02:10.803
- How about you? Busy night?
- Not really.

02:10.907 --> 02:14.700
Although mr. Krushenzo should
lighten things up for us.

02:14.807 --> 02:19.500
- Autoerotic asphyxiation, huh?
- God bless the weird ones.

02:19.606 --> 02:24.202
- What's this guy's deal?
- John Doe. No I.D.

02:24.307 --> 02:30.602
Nothing in the files. He's gonna
have to stay on ice until
somebody comes forward.

02:30.706 --> 02:33.302
He's missing his middle toe.

02:33.408 --> 02:35.803
That looks new.
Did you check records on him?

02:35.906 --> 02:40.000
Yeah, I did. He hadn't had
any foot surgery recently, so...

02:40.105 --> 02:42.901
I'm back at square zero.

02:43.008 --> 02:48.202
- Say hi to Melinda for me, will you?
- All right. Will do.

02:48.308 --> 02:50.801
Thanks, Harold.

02:50.906 --> 02:54.903
All right, you take it easy here.

